        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-12T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-12T22:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/5–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-13T12:00:00+09:00">May 13, 1948—noon.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 13—4:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>868. For Department and ECA. Embassy agrees entirely with statement general
                    policy contained Deptel 696, May 7 and will forward shortly its specific
                    recommendations re number and strategic location for advisors to Chinese
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Shanghai 379.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
